===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|+}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete}} The fact of being [[finished]] or [[perfected]]; [[completeness]]. {{defdate|Attested from the mid 16<sup>th</sup> century until the 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}
# The characteristic of being [[absolute]] in [[nature]] or [[scope]].
#: {{ux|en|the '''absoluteness''' of his sovereignty, the '''absoluteness''' of his convictions}}
# Absolute [[authority]], unlimited power; [[absolutism]], [[despotism]]. {{defdate|First attested in the 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}
#* {{RQ:Florio Montaigne Essayes|chapter=8|book=II|page=228|passage=I know no man that could produce more parts, both naturall and artificiall, fit to preserve his masterie, and to maintaine his '''absolutenesse''', than he doth; yet is hee cleane falne from them like a childe.}}
# The fact of being without qualifications or conditions; [[certainty]], unconditionality. {{defdate|First attested in the 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}
# Independent [[autonomy]]. {{defdate|First attested in the 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}

